4. Output Types

Every caught pattern should now be routed into one or more of these outputs:

A. Keep as-is

Pattern is strong and constructive.

B. Refine

Pattern is incomplete but promising.

C. Repurpose

Pattern is not useful in original form, but useful elsewhere.

D. Antidote

Pattern reveals a failure mode; generate a countermeasure.

E. Warning Artifact

Pattern is dangerous, misleading, manipulative, or corrosive; preserve as a labeled hazard example.

F. Meta-Pattern

Pattern is one instance of a recurring higher-order shape; store the abstract form.

G. Compost

Low-value debris, but still searchable as residue/training exhaust.

