16. Canonical Rules

Rule 1

Catch first. Judge second. Metabolize third.

Rule 2

Do not re-emit poison without labeling.

Rule 3

A broken pattern may still contain a useful invariant.

Rule 4

Antidotes must be simpler to deploy than the poison is to spread.

Rule 5

Preserve provenance so the system learns from residues, not just successes.

Rule 6

Meta-patterns matter more than isolated incidents.

